data.title: NBA Free Agency 2012: Nicolas Batum To Remain With Portland Trail Blazers
data.meta_description: The Portland Trailblazers have matched the offer sheet submitted by the Minnesota Timberwolves for Nicolas Batum.
data.text:
Robbie Hummel Agrees To Terms With Spanish Team Obradoiro Cab

On Wednesday afternoon, Minnesota Timberwolves draft pick Robbie Hummel announced via his personal twitter account that he will be playing for Obradoiro Cab of the first tier Spanish association, Liga ACB.

Timberwolves Free Agency: Draft Pick Robbie Hummel Could Play In Spain, According To Report

Minnesota Timberwolves second round draft pick Robbie Hummel is reportedly close to signing a contract with a Spanish team for the 2012-13 season.

NBA Free Agency 2012: Adelman Responds To Portland Comments About Batum Offer

Rick Adelman likes the team he has to coach with the Minnesota Timberwolves but he didn't like comments out of Portland regarding Minnesota's offer to restricted free agent Nicolas Batum.

NBA Free Agency: Timberwolves Offer For Ronnie Brewer Not Enough, According To Agent

According to Ronnie Brewer's agent, the Minnesota Timberwolves made a 'generous' offer to the guard before he eventually signed for the New York Knicks.

Timberwolves Free Agency 2012: Minnesota Forced To Play Waiting Game On Nicolas Batum

Having signed free agent Nicolas Batum to an offer sheet, all the Minnesota Timberwolves can do now is wait on the Portland Trail Blazers.

NBA Free Agency: Timberwolves Sign Nicolas Batum To Offer Sheet, Blazers Have Until Wednesday

The T-Wolves officially signed Nicolas Batum to an offer sheet on Sunday, and will now wait until Wednesday at 11:59 p.m. for the Blazers to match.

NBA Free Agency: Timberwolves Officially Amnesty Darko Milicic

The Minnesota Timberwolves have made it official: they've used the amnesty clause on Darko Milicic, to make room for the offer sheet tendered to Nicolas Batum.

NBA Trade Rumors: Timberwolves And Trail Blazers Discussing Move For Nicolas Batum

The latest NBA trade rumors involve the Minnesota Timberwolves and Portland Trail Blazers continuing to discuss a deal that would move restricted free agent Nicolas Batum. This one is bigger than the rest, though.

Timberwolves Have Nothing To Offer For Nicolas Batum, Says Trail Blazers GM

Portland Trail Blazers general manager Neil Olshey made it clear that Nicolas Batum will not be going to the Minnesota Timberwolves.

Timberwolves Trade Rumors: Minnesota 'Likely' To Land Bulls' Kyle Korver

The Minnesota Timberwolves are one of two teams who are in on the Kyle Korver sweepstakes, and it's looking likely that they'll be the team that lands the Bulls forward. A decision is expected by Sunday.
